 valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weighty Polearm</span><hr size=1> Is it really better than a BaH (40 / 48 ) + 4 mg dmg if proc?  Higher delay = higher dmg bonus... <br>
<br>
What do you all think?  Cuz i currently have a BaH and can pick up a weighty polearm for about 150 pp on BB. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 366<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/03 5:40:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4818.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   BAH still good</span><hr size=1> The Black Acrylia Halberd is still one of the best weapons you can buy for soloing. It's long delay cuts down on riposte damage. It's good ratio puts out good DPS. And the lifetap really really helps during fights.<br>
<br>
The Weighty Polearm's a great weapon, and really it's price is only as low as it is because of Windblade and because the polearm's a rather common drop from a tier 1 zone that everyone has access to.<br>
<br>
But the Halberd's still a damn good weapon.<br>
<br>
